## 📑 Internship Worklog Introduction

During this laboratory phase of the AWS Cloud Training internship program, I have systematically approached, researched, and successfully deployed core infrastructure services on the AWS Cloud ecosystem. 

This comprehensive worklog is scheduled across **12 weeks** (spanning the entire duration of the corporate placement). It documents my step-by-step engineering journey, tracking theoretical insights, practical laboratory milestones, system architecture designs, and real-world troubleshooting experiences. The timeline and major achievements for each active week are structured as follows:

---

## 📅 Weekly Log Directory

**Week 1:** [Cloud Fundamentals & AWS IAM Security Essentials](1.1-week1/)
* Overview of Cloud Computing models and establishing root access boundaries using IAM Users, Groups, and Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA).

**Week 2:** [Amazon EC2 Virtual Compute Deployments & Firewalls](1.2-week2/)
* Launching Linux Ubuntu Server environments, managing cryptographic Key Pairs, and configuring stateful Security Group firewall rules.

**Week 3:** [Amazon S3 Global Object Storage & Web Hosting](1.3-week3/)
* Deploying globally unique storage buckets, controlling object lifecycles, activating Buckets Versioning, and launching Static Website Hosting.

**Week 4:** [Custom Amazon VPC Network Topology Engineering](1.4-week4/)
* Architecting isolated cloud network spaces, structuring Public and Private Subnet topologies, routing tables, Internet Gateways, and NAT Gateways.

**Week 5 & 6:** [Hybrid Storage Gateway Integrations & Enterprise GenAIOps Event](1.5-week5/)
* Implementing AWS Storage Gateway (SMB File Share) with Windows Server and gathering enterprise insights into Multi-Agent AI and FinOps budgets at AWS Vietnam Community Day.

**Week 7:** [High Availability Architectures & Automated CI/CD Pipelines](1.7-week7/)
* Engineering self-healing architectures via Load Balancers (ALB) and Auto Scaling Groups (ASG), containerizing with Docker (ECS Fargate), and orchestrating AWS Developer tool pipelines.

**Week 8:** [Cloud Databases & Modern Serverless System Design](1.8-week8/)
* Provisioning Relational Databases (Amazon RDS MySQL), NoSQL engines (DynamoDB), Serverless compute (AWS Lambda), and mapping out the 3-Tier Architecture Mini Project blueprint.

**Week 9:** [Advanced Stateless Authentication & Internal AWS Technical Tournament](1.9-week9/)
* Integrating Amazon Cognito identity authorizers with API Gateway, auditing API trails via CloudTrail, and analyzing real-world troubleshooting scenarios during the internal tech competition.

**Week 10:** [Cloud Financial Governance, Multi-Region Audits & Clean-Up](1.10-week10/)
* Mastering AWS Budgets and cost management dashboards, conducting global multi-region resource sweeps, and safely de-provisioning assets to complete the laboratory training phase.

